    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Can the tests do a \"roundtrip\" using `fn.keytrans()`, or something like that, to double-check each assertion?\r\n\r\n> The reason for doing it trough lua rather than using c with the already existing functions, is that through c, much more complexity would be needed to implement the feature.\r\n\r\nAre you sure? We have about 5+ related functions already, so want to be certain that we need yet another implementation. \r\n\r\nWhy can't [`replace_termcodes`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0a3add979a2689843673301044a14b3484d9d96f/src/nvim/keycodes.c#L663) optionally build a API `Object` ? I would not expect that to severely complicate it.",
